  "prompt": "How can I report someone on Quora?",
  "response": "Reporting someone on Quora is relatively straightforward. Follow these steps to report a user:\n\n1. **Visit the user\u2019s profile:** Navigate to the profile of the person you want to report.\n\n2. **Access the \u2018More\u2019 menu:** On the user\u2019s profile page, click on the three dots typically located near the top-right corner of the profile header or next to their name/profile picture.\n\n3. **Select \u2018Report\u2019 option:** From the dropdown menu, select the option that says \u2018Report\u2019.\n\n4. **Choose the reason for reporting:** You will be asked to select the reason for reporting the user. Choose the most appropriate reason that fits the issue you are reporting.\n\n5. **Provide additional details:** If prompted, provide further details or descriptions of the issue to help Quora moderators understand the situation better.\n\nRemember, this feature is intended for serious issues such as harassment, spam, or inappropriate content. Users are encouraged to use it responsibly.\n\nIf you have trouble following these steps or need additional assistance, you can visit Quora's Help Center for more detailed guidance.",
